{"type":"text","timestamp":1775898114590,"sessionID":"ses_2843d4176ffeAKdOiytawM05uH","part":{"id":"prt_d7bc3e317001SAt3kdwHsyI5K0","messageID":"msg_d7bc3c917001Bdml7F12m1LUja","sessionID":"ses_2843d4176ffeAKdOiytawM05uH","type":"text","text":"Now I'll write the design.md file with comprehensive technical implementation details:","time":{"start":1775898114587,"end":1775898114587}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775898114751,"sessionID":"ses_2843d4176ffeAKdOiytawM05uH","part":{"id":"prt_d7bc6ba1f001qFVkEMud9q6uVV","messageID":"msg_d7bc3c917001Bdml7F12m1LUja","sessionID":"ses_2843d4176ffeAKdOiytawM05uH","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-ad01161d468a4cba869ea63b2bb2f08f","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md","content":"# Design Document: Go Unit Tests for router/store/picod (AR-039)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document outlines the technical implementation details for comprehensive unit testing of the agentcube project's core modules: `pkg/router`, `pkg/store`, and `pkg/picod`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Architecture Overview\n\n### Module Dependencies\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         pkg/router                               │\n│  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐              │\n│  │  Server  │──│SessionManager│──│   JWTManager   │              │\n│  └────┬─────┘  └──────┬───────┘  └────────────────┘              │\n│       │               │                                          │\n│       ▼               ▼                                          │\n│  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐   │\n│  │Middleware│  │ReversePro│  │   Config    │  │    Errors    │   │\n│  │          │  │ xy       │  │             │  │              │   │\n│  └──────────┘  └──────────┘  └─────────────┘  └──────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         pkg/store                                │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐   │\n│  │   Store      │──│   redisStore   │──│    valkeyStore      │   │\n│  │  Interface   │  │                │  │                     │   │\n│  └──────────────┘  └────────────────┘  └─────────────────────┘   │\n│  Keys: session:{id}, session:expiry (ZSET), session:last_activity│\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         pkg/picod                                │\n│  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────┐  │\n│  │  Server  │──│ AuthManager  │──│   Execute   │──│  Files   │  │\n│  │          │  │              │  │  Handler    │  │ Handler  │  │\n│  └──────────┘  └──────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └──────────┘  │\n│  ┌─────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │   sanitize  │──│   health   │──│         Config           │  │\n│  │             │  │            │  │                          │  │\n│  └─────────────┘  └────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 pkg/router Data Structures\n\n```go\n// Server (pkg/router/server.go)\ntype Server struct {\n    config         *Config\n    engine         *gin.Engine\n    httpServer     *http.Server\n    sessionManager SessionManager\n    storeClient    Store\n    httpTransport  *http.Transport\n    jwtManager     *JWTManager\n    logger         Logger\n}\n\n// Config (pkg/router/config.go)\ntype Config struct {\n    Port                  string\n    EnableTLS             bool\n    TLSCert               string\n    TLSKey                string\n    MaxConcurrentRequests int\n    Debug                 bool\n}\n\n// RouterClaims (pkg/router/jwt.go)\ntype RouterClaims struct {\n    SessionID string `json:\"session_id\"`\n    SandboxID string `json:\"sandbox_id\"`\n    Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n    Name      string `json:\"name\"`\n    jwt.RegisteredClaims\n}\n\n// TokenPair (pkg/router/jwt.go)\ntype TokenPair struct {\n    AccessToken  string `json:\"access_token\"`\n    RefreshToken string `json:\"refresh_token\"`\n    ExpiresIn    int64  `json:\"expires_in\"`\n    TokenType    string `json:\"token_type\"`\n}\n\n// JWTManager (pkg/router/jwt.go)\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n    k8sClient  kubernetes.Interface\n    config     *JWTConfig\n}\n```\n\n### 2.2 pkg/store Data Structures\n\n```go\n// Store Interface (pkg/store/store.go)\ntype Store interface {\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    Close() error\n}\n\n// redisStore (pkg/store/store_redis.go)\ntype redisStore struct {\n    cli                  *redisv9.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string     // \"session:\"\n    expiryIndexKey       string     // \"session:expiry\" (ZSET)\n    lastActivityIndexKey string     // \"session:last_activity\" (ZSET)\n}\n\n// valkeyStore (pkg/store/store_valkey.go)\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n\n// Error types\nvar (\n    ErrNotFound         = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n    ErrNilSandbox       = errors.New(\"store: sandbox is nil\")\n    ErrZeroExpiresAt    = errors.New(\"store: expiresAt is required\")\n    ErrEmptySessionID   = errors.New(\"store: sessionID is required\")\n    ErrInvalidProvider  = errors.New(\"store: invalid provider type\")\n    ErrPasswordRequired = errors.New(\"store: password is required\")\n    ErrKeyNotExists     = errors.New(\"store: key not exists\")\n    ErrSessionExists    = errors.New(\"store: session already exists\")\n)\n```\n\n### 2.3 pkg/picod Data Structures\n\n```go\n// Server (pkg/picod/server.go)\ntype Server struct {\n    config      *Config\n    engine      *gin.Engine\n    httpServer  *http.Server\n    authManager *AuthManager\n    workspace   string\n    startTime   time.Time\n}\n\n// Config (pkg/picod/config.go)\ntype Config struct {\n    Port      int\n    Workspace string\n}\n\n// AuthManager (pkg/picod/auth.go)\ntype AuthManager struct {\n    publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n    mutex     sync.RWMutex\n}\n\n// ExecuteRequest/Response (pkg/picod/execute.go)\ntype ExecuteRequest struct {\n    Command    []string          `json:\"command\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Timeout    string            `json:\"timeout\"`\n    WorkingDir string            `json:\"working_dir\"`\n    Env        map[string]string `json:\"env\"`\n}\n\ntype ExecuteResponse struct {\n    Stdout    string    `json:\"stdout\"`\n    Stderr    string    `json:\"stderr\"`\n    ExitCode  int       `json:\"exit_code\"`\n    Duration  float64   `json:\"duration\"`\n    StartTime time.Time `json:\"start_time\"`\n    EndTime   time.Time `json:\"end_time\"`\n}\n\n// FileInfo/FileEntry (pkg/picod/files.go)\ntype FileInfo struct {\n    Path     string    `json:\"path\"`\n    Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n    Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n    Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n}\n\ntype FileEntry struct {\n    Name     string    `json:\"name\"`\n    Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n    Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n    Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n    IsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n}\n\ntype ListFilesResponse struct {\n    Files []FileEntry `json:\"files\"`\n    Path  string      `json:\"path\"`\n}\n```\n\n### 2.4 pkg/common/types Data Structures\n\n```go\n// SandboxInfo (pkg/common/types/sandbox.go)\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    Kind               string              `json:\"kind\"`\n    SandboxID          string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxNamespace   string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n    SandboxName        string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n    Name               string              `json:\"name\"`\n    SessionID          string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    CreatedAt          time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt          time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    Status             string              `json:\"status\"`\n    EntryPoints        []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n    UserToken          string              `json:\"userToken,omitempty\"`\n    ServiceAccount     string              `json:\"serviceAccount,omitempty\"`\n    ServiceAccountName string              `json:\"serviceAccountName,omitempty\"`\n    LastActivity       time.Time           `json:\"lastActivity,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n    Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n}\n\n// Kind constants\nconst (\n    AgentRuntimeKind    = \"AgentRuntime\"\n    CodeInterpreterKind = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n    SandboxKind         = \"Sandbox\"\n    SandboxClaimKind    = \"SandboxClaim\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 Router HTTP Endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Handler | Purpose |\n|----------|--------|---------|---------|\n| `/health/live` | GET | `handleHealthLive` | Liveness probe |\n| `/health/ready` | GET | `handleHealthReady` | Readiness probe |\n| `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | `handleAgentInvoke` | Agent runtime invocation |\n| `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` | Code interpreter invocation |\n\n**Request Headers:**\n- `x-agentcube-session-id`: Session identifier (optional)\n\n**Response Headers (proxy):**\n- `x-agentcube-session-id`: Echoed session ID\n\n### 3.2 PicoD HTTP Endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Handler | Auth Required |\n|----------|--------|---------|---------------|\n| `/health` | GET | `HealthCheckHandler` | No |\n| `/api/execute` | POST | `ExecuteHandler` | Yes (JWT) |\n| `/api/files` | POST | `UploadFileHandler` | Yes (JWT) |\n| `/api/files` | GET | `ListFilesHandler` | Yes (JWT) |\n| `/api/files/*path` | GET | `DownloadFileHandler` | Yes (JWT) |\n\n**Execute API Contract:**\n```json\n// Request\n{\n    \"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello\"],\n    \"timeout\": \"5s\",\n    \"working_dir\": \"subdir\",\n    \"env\": {\"MY_VAR\": \"value\"}\n}\n\n// Response\n{\n    \"stdout\": \"hello\\n\",\n    \"stderr\": \"\",\n    \"exit_code\": 0,\n    \"duration\": 0.01,\n    \"start_time\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n    \"end_time\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:01Z\"\n}\n```\n\n**Files Upload API Contract:**\n```json\n// JSON Request\n{\n    \"path\": \"test.txt\",\n    \"content\": \"base64-encoded-content\",\n    \"mode\": \"0644\"\n}\n\n// Response\n{\n    \"path\": \"test.txt\",\n    \"size\": 12,\n    \"mode\": \"0644\",\n    \"modified\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n### 3.3 Store Interface Contract\n\n| Method | Input | Output | Error Conditions |\n|--------|-------|--------|------------------|\n| `Ping` | `ctx` | `error` | Connection failure |\n| `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `ctx, sessionID` | `*SandboxInfo, error` | Empty sessionID, not found |\n| `StoreSandbox` | `ctx, *SandboxInfo` | `error` | Nil sandbox, empty sessionID, zero expiresAt, session exists |\n| `UpdateSandbox` | `ctx, *SandboxInfo` | `error` | Nil sandbox, empty sessionID, not found |\n| `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `ctx, sessionID` | `error` | Empty sessionID |\n| `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `ctx, before, limit` | `[]*SandboxInfo, error` | Zero/negative limit returns nil |\n| `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `ctx, before, limit` | `[]*SandboxInfo, error` | Zero/negative limit returns nil |\n| `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `ctx, sessionID, at` | `error` | Empty sessionID, session not found |\n| `Close` | - | `error` | - |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Error Handling Strategy\n\n### 4.1 Router Error Types (pkg/router/errors.go)\n\n```go\ntype APIStatus interface {\n    Status() int\n    Code() string\n    Message() string\n}\n```\n\n| Error Type | Status | Code | Condition |\n|------------|--------|------|-----------|\n| `SessionNotFoundError` | 404 | SESSION_NOT_FOUND | Session not in store |\n| `SandboxUnreachableError` | 502 | SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE | Connection refused |\n| `SandboxTimeoutError` | 504 | SANDBOX_TIMEOUT | Timeout exceeded |\n| `JWTSigningError` | 500 | JWT_SIGNING_FAILED | Token signing failure |\n| `JWTValidationError` | 401 | JWT_VALIDATION_FAILED | Token validation failure |\n| `JWTTokenExpiredError` | 401 | JWT_TOKEN_EXPIRED | Token expired |\n| `JWTTokenMissingError` | 401 | JWT_TOKEN_MISSING | No Authorization header |\n| `JWTInvalidFormatError` | 401 | JWT_INVALID_FORMAT | Malformed auth header |\n| `JWTKeyLoadError` | 500 | JWT_KEY_LOAD_FAILED | Key load failure |\n| `ServerOverloadedError` | 429 | SERVER_OVERLOADED | Concurrency limit exceeded |\n| `NoEntryPointError` | 404 | NO_ENTRY_POINT | No entry point configured |\n| `WorkloadManagerError` | varies | WORKLOAD_MANAGER_ERROR | Workload manager failure |\n\n### 4.2 PicoD Error Responses\n\n| Endpoint | Status | Error Message | Condition |\n|----------|--------|---------------|-----------|\n| Auth Middleware | 401 | `missing authorization header` | No header |\n| Auth Middleware | 401 | `invalid token format` | Malformed header |\n| Auth Middleware | 401 | `token is expired` | JWT expired |\n| Auth Middleware | 401 | `invalid signature` | Signature mismatch |\n| Auth Middleware | 401 | `invalid signing method` | Non-RS256 |\n| Execute | 400 | `invalid request body` | JSON parse error |\n| Execute | 400 | `missing command` | Empty command array |\n| Execute | 400 | `invalid working directory` | Path escape |\n| Files Upload | 400 | `missing path parameter` | No path |\n| Files Upload | 400 | `missing file` | No multipart file |\n| Files Upload | 400 | `invalid base64 content` | Base64 decode error |\n| Files Upload | 400 | `invalid path` | Path escape |\n| Files Upload | 400 | `invalid file mode` | Mode > 0777 |\n| Files List | 400 | `missing path parameter` | No path query |\n| Files List | 400 | `invalid path` | Path escape |\n| Files List | 500 | `failed to read directory` | Directory not found |\n| Files Download | 400 | `invalid path` | Path escape |\n| Files Download | 400 | `path is not a file` | Path is directory |\n| Files Download | 404 | `file not found` | File not exists |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Test Coverage Requirements\n\n| Module | Target Coverage | Priority |\n|--------|-----------------|----------|\n| pkg/router | 90% | High |\n| pkg/store | 95% | High |\n| pkg/picod | 90% | High |\n| pkg/common/types | 100% | Medium |\n\n### 5.2 Test Categories\n\n#### 5.2.1 Unit Tests (Pure Logic)\n\n**router:**\n- JWT token generation/validation\n- Error type methods (Status, Code, Message)\n- Config defaults\n- Reverse proxy URL building\n- Entry point selection logic\n- Path sanitization\n\n**store:**\n- Store interface implementation\n- Error types and messages\n- Key generation (sessionKey)\n- Redis/Valkey client configuration\n- Singleton pattern (Storage/ResetStorage)\n\n**picod:**\n- Path sanitization\n- File mode parsing\n- JWT public key loading\n- Auth middleware logic\n\n#### 5.2.2 Integration Tests (HTTP Handlers)\n\n**router:**\n- Server initialization\n- Route registration\n- Health endpoints\n- TLS configuration\n- Graceful shutdown\n- Concurrency limits\n- Proxy request handling\n- Session manager integration\n\n**picod:**\n- Execute handler (command execution, timeout, exit codes)\n- File upload/download/list operations\n- Authentication flow\n- Health check endpoint\n\n#### 5.2.3 Mock-Based Tests\n\n**Mock Types Required:**\n\n```go\n// pkg/router mocks\ntype MockStore struct {\n    GetSandboxBySessionIDFunc     func(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandboxFunc              func(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandboxFunc             func(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSessionLastActivityFunc func(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionIDFunc  func(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n}\n\ntype MockSessionManager struct {\n    GetSandboxBySessionFunc func(ctx context.Context, sessionID, namespace, name, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n\ntype MockLogger struct {\n    InfoCalls    []string\n    ErrorCalls   []string\n    WarningCalls []string\n}\n\ntype MockHTTPClient struct {\n    DoFunc func(req *http.Request) (*http.Response, error)\n}\n\n// pkg/picod mocks\ntype MockAuthManager struct {\n    ValidateTokenFunc func(token string) error\n}\n```\n\n### 5.3 Test Helper Functions\n\n```go\n// pkg/router test helpers\nfunc setupTestRouter(t *testing.T) *Server\nfunc makeTestRequest(method, path string, body io.Reader) *http.Request\n\n// pkg/store test helpers (already exists)\nfunc setupTestRedisStore(t *testing.T) *redisStore\nfunc makeTestSandbox(sessionID string) *types.SandboxInfo\n\n// pkg/picod test helpers (already exists)\nfunc setupTestServer(t *testing.T) *Server\nfunc encodePublicKeyPEMForTest(key *rsa.PublicKey) string\nfunc generateTestJWT(privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey, expired bool) string\nfunc makeAuthenticatedRequest(t *testing.T, server *Server, method, path string, body io.Reader, contentType string, jwtToken string) *httptest.ResponseRecorder\n```\n\n### 5.4 miniredis Usage for Store Tests\n\n```go\nimport \"github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2\"\n\nfunc setupTestRedisStore(t *testing.T) *redisStore {\n    mr := miniredis.RunT(t)\n    cli := redisv9.NewClient(&redisv9.Options{\n        Addr: mr.Addr(),\n    })\n    return &redisStore{\n        cli:                  cli,\n        sessionPrefix:        defaultSessionPrefix,\n        expiryIndexKey:       defaultExpiryIndexKey,\n        lastActivityIndexKey: defaultLastActivityIndexKey,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Test Implementation Details\n\n### 6.1 pkg/router Tests\n\n#### 6.1.1 JWT Manager Tests (jwt_test.go)\n\n```go\n// Tests needed:\nfunc TestJWTManagerGenerateToken(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestJWTManagerGenerateTokenWithClaims(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestJWTManagerGenerateTokenPair(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestJWTManagerValidateToken(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestJWTManagerValidateTokenExpired(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestJWTManagerValidateTokenInvalidSignature(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestJWTManagerValidateTokenMalformed(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestJWTManagerRefreshToken(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestJWTManagerRefreshTokenNotRefreshToken(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestJWTManagerGetPublicKeyPEM(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestJWTManagerFromPrivateKeyNil(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestJWTManagerWithConfig(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestEncodePrivateKeyPEM(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestEncodePublicKeyPEM(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestLoadPrivateKeyPEM(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestLoadPrivateKeyPEMInvalid(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestRouterClaims(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestJWTConfigDefaults(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n#### 6.1.2 Config Tests (config_test.go)\n\n```go\nfunc TestDefaultConfig(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestConfigPortDefault(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestConfigTLSFields(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestConfigDebugMode(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestConfigMaxConcurrentRequestsDefault(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n#### 6.1.3 Middleware Tests (middleware_test.go) - Already comprehensive\n\nCoverage includes:\n- Concurrency limit under/over limit\n- Default/negative limit handling\n- Logging middleware with nil lo