{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775898260634,"sessionID":"ses_2843d4176ffeAKdOiytawM05uH","part":{"id":"prt_d7bc8f441001AJlXI0DFGu9DJQ","messageID":"msg_d7bc6f9f7001IhZRImDzxAmDvS","sessionID":"ses_2843d4176ffeAKdOiytawM05uH","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-fe4e0c20caa9425e9f53c2f22ebcb458","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-039/design.md","content":"# AR-039 — Go 单元测试 (router/store/picod) Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-039 — Go 单元测试 (router/store/picod) |\n| Module | pkg |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-2 |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Module Dependencies\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         pkg/router                               │\n│  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐              │\n│  │  Server  │──│SessionManager│──│   JWTManager   │              │\n│  └────┬─────┘  └──────┬───────┘  └────────────────┘              │\n│       │               │                                          │\n│       ▼               ▼                                          │\n│  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐   │\n│  │Middleware│  │ReversePro│  │   Config    │  │    Errors    │   │\n│  │          │  │ xy       │  │             │  │              │   │\n│  └──────────┘  └──────────┘  └─────────────┘  └──────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         pkg/store                                │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐   │\n│  │   Store      │──│   redisStore   │──│    valkeyStore      │   │\n│  │  Interface   │  │                │  │                     │   │\n│  └──────────────┘  └────────────────┘  └─────────────────────┘   │\n│  Keys: session:{id}, session:expiry (ZSET), session:last_activity│\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         pkg/picod                                │\n│  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────┐  │\n│  │  Server  │──│ AuthManager  │──│   Execute   │──│  Files   │  │\n│  │          │  │              │  │  Handler    │  │ Handler  │  │\n│  └──────────┘  └──────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └──────────┘  │\n│  ┌─────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │   sanitize  │──│   health   │──│         Config           │  │\n│  │             │  │            │  │                          │  │\n│  └─────────────┘  └────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Test Architecture\n\n```\n                    ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n                    │         Test Categories             │\n                    └─────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                     │\n           ┌─────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────┐\n           │                         │                         │\n           ▼                         ▼                         ▼\n    ┌──────────────┐          ┌──────────────┐          ┌──────────────┐\n    │  Unit Tests  │          │ Integration  │          │  Mock Tests  │\n    │  (Pure)      │          │   Tests      │          │              │\n    └──────────────┘          └──────────────┘          └──────────────┘\n           │                         │                         │\n           ▼                         ▼                         ▼\n    - JWT logic                - HTTP handlers            - MockStore\n    - Error types              - Server init              - MockSessionMgr\n    - Config                   - Graceful shutdown        - MockLogger\n    - Path sanitization        - Route registration       - MockHTTPClient\n    - Key generation           - Proxy handling           - FakeK8sClient\n\n                    ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n                    │      Test Infrastructure            │\n                    └─────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                     │\n           ┌─────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────┐\n           │                         │                         │\n           ▼                         ▼                         ▼\n    ┌──────────────┐          ┌──────────────┐          ┌──────────────┐\n    │  miniredis   │          │ httptest     │          │  testify    │\n    │  (Redis mock)│          │  (HTTP mock) │          │  (assert)   │\n    └──────────────┘          └──────────────┘          └──────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### pkg/router\n\n```go\n// Server (pkg/router/server.go)\ntype Server struct {\n    config         *Config\n    engine         *gin.Engine\n    httpServer     *http.Server\n    sessionManager SessionManager\n    storeClient    Store\n    httpTransport  *http.Transport\n    jwtManager     *JWTManager\n    logger         Logger\n}\n\n// Config (pkg/router/config.go)\ntype Config struct {\n    Port                  string\n    EnableTLS             bool\n    TLSCert               string\n    TLSKey                string\n    MaxConcurrentRequests int\n    Debug                 bool\n}\n\n// RouterClaims (pkg/router/jwt.go)\ntype RouterClaims struct {\n    SessionID string `json:\"session_id\"`\n    SandboxID string `json:\"sandbox_id\"`\n    Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n    Name      string `json:\"name\"`\n    jwt.RegisteredClaims\n}\n\n// JWTManager (pkg/router/jwt.go)\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n    k8sClient  kubernetes.Interface\n    config     *JWTConfig\n}\n\n// sessionManager (pkg/router/session_manager.go)\ntype sessionManager struct {\n    storeClient     Store\n    workloadMgrAddr string\n    httpClient      *http.Client\n}\n\n// ReverseProxyWrapper (pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go)\ntype ReverseProxyWrapper struct {\n    director       func(*http.Request)\n    modifyResponse func(*http.Response) error\n    errorHandler   func(http.ResponseWriter, *http.Request, error)\n}\n```\n\n### pkg/store\n\n```go\n// Store Interface (pkg/store/store.go)\ntype Store interface {\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    Close() error\n}\n\n// redisStore (pkg/store/store_redis.go)\ntype redisStore struct {\n    cli                  *redisv9.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string     // Default: \"session:\"\n    expiryIndexKey       string     // Default: \"session:expiry\" (ZSET)\n    lastActivityIndexKey string     // Default: \"session:last_activity\" (ZSET)\n}\n\n// valkeyStore (pkg/store/store_valkey.go)\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n\n// Error constants\nvar (\n    ErrNotFound         = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n    ErrNilSandbox       = errors.New(\"store: sandbox is nil\")\n    ErrZeroExpiresAt    = errors.New(\"store: expiresAt is required\")\n    ErrEmptySessionID   = errors.New(\"store: sessionID is required\")\n    ErrInvalidProvider  = errors.New(\"store: invalid provider type\")\n    ErrPasswordRequired = errors.New(\"store: password is required\")\n    ErrKeyNotExists     = errors.New(\"store: key not exists\")\n    ErrSessionExists    = errors.New(\"store: session already exists\")\n)\n```\n\n### pkg/picod\n\n```go\n// Server (pkg/picod/server.go)\ntype Server struct {\n    config      *Config\n    engine      *gin.Engine\n    httpServer  *http.Server\n    authManager *AuthManager\n    workspace   string\n    startTime   time.Time\n}\n\n// Config (pkg/picod/config.go)\ntype Config struct {\n    Port      int\n    Workspace string\n}\n\n// AuthManager (pkg/picod/auth.go)\ntype AuthManager struct {\n    publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n    mutex     sync.RWMutex\n}\n\n// ExecuteRequest/Response (pkg/picod/execute.go)\ntype ExecuteRequest struct {\n    Command    []string          `json:\"command\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Timeout    string            `json:\"timeout\"`\n    WorkingDir string            `json:\"working_dir\"`\n    Env        map[string]string `json:\"env\"`\n}\n\ntype ExecuteResponse struct {\n    Stdout    string    `json:\"stdout\"`\n    Stderr    string    `json:\"stderr\"`\n    ExitCode  int       `json:\"exit_code\"`\n    Duration  float64   `json:\"duration\"`\n    StartTime time.Time `json:\"start_time\"`\n    EndTime   time.Time `json:\"end_time\"`\n}\n\n// FileInfo/FileEntry (pkg/picod/files.go)\ntype FileInfo struct {\n    Path     string    `json:\"path\"`\n    Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n    Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n    Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n}\n\ntype FileEntry struct {\n    Name     string    `json:\"name\"`\n    Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n    Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n    Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n    IsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n}\n\ntype ListFilesResponse struct {\n    Files []FileEntry `json:\"files\"`\n    Path  string      `json:\"path\"`\n}\n```\n\n### pkg/common/types\n\n```go\n// SandboxInfo (pkg/common/types/sandbox.go)\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    Kind               string              `json:\"kind\"`\n    SandboxID          string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxNamespace   string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n    SandboxName        string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n    Name               string              `json:\"name\"`\n    SessionID          string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    CreatedAt          time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt          time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    Status             string              `json:\"status\"`\n    EntryPoints        []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n    UserToken          string              `json:\"userToken,omitempty\"`\n    ServiceAccount     string              `json:\"serviceAccount,omitempty\"`\n    ServiceAccountName string              `json:\"serviceAccountName,omitempty\"`\n    LastActivity       time.Time           `json:\"lastActivity,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n    Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n}\n\n// Kind constants\nconst (\n    AgentRuntimeKind    = \"AgentRuntime\"\n    CodeInterpreterKind = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n    SandboxKind         = \"Sandbox\"\n    SandboxClaimKind    = \"SandboxClaim\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Router HTTP Endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Handler | Purpose |\n|----------|--------|---------|---------|\n| `/health/live` | GET | `handleHealthLive` | Liveness probe - returns 200 with `{\"status\": \"alive\"}` |\n| `/health/ready` | GET | `handleHealthReady` | Readiness probe - returns 200 if sessionManager available |\n| `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | `handleAgentInvoke` | Agent runtime invocation proxy |\n| `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` | Code interpreter invocation proxy |\n\n**Router Request Headers:**\n- `x-agentcube-session-id`: Session identifier (optional, triggers new session creation if empty)\n\n**Router Response Headers (proxy):**\n- `x-agentcube-session-id`: Echoed session ID for client tracking\n\n### PicoD HTTP Endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Handler | Auth Required |\n|----------|--------|---------|---------------|\n| `/health` | GET | `HealthCheckHandler` | No - returns service status |\n| `/api/execute` | POST | `ExecuteHandler` | Yes (RS256 JWT) |\n| `/api/files` | POST | `UploadFileHandler` | Yes (RS256 JWT) |\n| `/api/files` | GET | `ListFilesHandler` | Yes (RS256 JWT) |\n| `/api/files/*path` | GET | `DownloadFileHandler` | Yes (RS256 JWT) |\n\n**Execute API Contract:**\n```json\n// Request\n{\n    \"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello\"],\n    \"timeout\": \"5s\",\n    \"working_dir\": \"subdir\",\n    \"env\": {\"MY_VAR\": \"value\"}\n}\n\n// Response (200 OK)\n{\n    \"stdout\": \"hello\\n\",\n    \"stderr\": \"\",\n    \"exit_code\": 0,\n    \"duration\": 0.01,\n    \"start_time\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n    \"end_time\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:01Z\"\n}\n\n// Timeout Response (200 OK)\n{\n    \"stdout\": \"\",\n    \"stderr\": \"command timed out\",\n    \"exit_code\": 124,\n    ...\n}\n```\n\n**Files Upload API Contract (JSON):**\n```json\n// Request\n{\n    \"path\": \"test.txt\",\n    \"content\": \"base64-encoded-content\",\n    \"mode\": \"0644\"\n}\n\n// Response (200 OK)\n{\n    \"path\": \"test.txt\",\n    \"size\": 12,\n    \"mode\": \"0644\",\n    \"modified\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n**Files Upload API Contract (multipart/form-data):**\n- Form field `path`: Required, file destination path\n- Form field `file`: Required, file content\n- Form field `mode`: Optional, file permissions (octal string)\n\n### Store Interface Contract\n\n| Method | Input | Output | Error Conditions |\n|--------|-------|--------|------------------|\n| `Ping` | `ctx` | `error` | Connection failure, unexpected response |\n| `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `ctx, sessionID` | `*SandboxInfo, error` | `ErrEmptySessionID`, `ErrNotFound`, JSON parse error |\n| `StoreSandbox` | `ctx, *SandboxInfo` | `error` | `ErrNilSandbox`, `ErrEmptySessionID`, `ErrZeroExpiresAt`, `ErrSessionExists` |\n| `UpdateSandbox` | `ctx, *SandboxInfo` | `error` | `ErrNilSandbox`, `ErrEmptySessionID`, `ErrNotFound` |\n| `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `ctx, sessionID` | `error` | `ErrEmptySessionID` |\n| `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `ctx, before, limit` | `[]*SandboxInfo, error` | Zero/negative limit → nil, nil |\n| `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `ctx, before, limit` | `[]*SandboxInfo, error` | Zero/negative limit → nil, nil |\n| `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `ctx, sessionID, at` | `error` | `ErrEmptySessionID`, `ErrNotFound` |\n| `Close` | - | `error` | Close failure |\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Router Error Types (pkg/router/errors.go)\n\nAll router errors implement the `APIStatus` interface:\n\n```go\ntype APIStatus interface {\n    Status() int    // HTTP status code\n    Code() string   // Error code for client parsing\n    Message() string // Human-readable message\n}\n```\n\n| Error Type | Status | Code | Condition |\n|------------|--------|------|-----------|\n| `SessionNotFoundError` | 404 | SESSION_NOT_FOUND | Session not in store |\n| `SandboxUnreachableError` | 502 | SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE | Connection refused to sandbox |\n| `SandboxTimeoutError` | 504 | SANDBOX_TIMEOUT | Request timeout to sandbox |\n| `JWTSigningError` | 500 | JWT_SIGNING_FAILED | Token signing failure |\n| `JWTValidationError` | 401 | JWT_VALIDATION_FAILED | Token validation failure |\n| `JWTTokenExpiredError` | 401 | JWT_TOKEN_EXPIRED | Token expired |\n| `JWTTokenMissingError` | 401 | JWT_TOKEN_MISSING | No Authorization header |\n| `JWTInvalidFormatError` | 401 | JWT_INVALID_FORMAT | Malformed auth header |\n| `JWTKeyLoadError` | 500 | JWT_KEY_LOAD_FAILED | RSA key load failure |\n| `ServerOverloadedError` | 429 | SERVER_OVERLOADED | Concurrency limit exceeded |\n| `NoEntryPointError` | 404 | NO_ENTRY_POINT | No entry point configured |\n| `WorkloadManagerError` | varies | WORKLOAD_MANAGER_ERROR | Workload manager failure |\n\n### PicoD Error Responses\n\n| Endpoint | Status | Error Message | Condition |\n|----------|--------|---------------|-----------|\n| Auth Middleware | 401 | `missing authorization header` | No `Authorization` header |\n| Auth Middleware | 401 | `invalid token format` | Missing \"Bearer \" prefix |\n| Auth Middleware | 401 | `token is expired` | JWT `exp` claim past |\n| Auth Middleware | 401 | `invalid signature` | Signature verification failed |\n| Auth Middleware | 401 | `invalid signing method` | Non-RS256 algorithm |\n| Execute | 400 | `invalid request body` | JSON parse failure |\n| Execute | 400 | `missing command` | Empty `command` array |\n| Execute | 400 | `invalid working directory` | Path escape detected |\n| Files Upload | 400 | `missing path parameter` | No `path` field |\n| Files Upload | 400 | `missing file` | No multipart `file` field |\n| Files Upload | 400 | `invalid base64 content` | Base64 decode failure |\n| Files Upload | 400 | `invalid path` | Path escape detected |\n| Files Upload | 400 | `invalid file mode` | Mode > 0777 |\n| Files List | 400 | `missing path parameter` | No `path` query param |\n| Files List | 400 | `invalid path` | Path escape detected |\n| Files List | 500 | `failed to read directory` | Directory not readable |\n| Files Download | 400 | `invalid path` | Path escape detected |\n| Files Download | 400 | `path is not a file` | Path is directory |\n| Files Download | 404 | `file not found` | File does not exist |\n\n### Store Error Handling\n\n| Error | Return Condition |\n|-------|-----------------|\n| `ErrNotFound` | Key not found in Redis/Valkey |\n| `ErrNilSandbox` | nil sandbox passed to Store/Update |\n| `ErrZeroExpiresAt` | ExpiresAt is time.Time{} |\n| `ErrEmptySessionID` | SessionID is empty string |\n| `ErrPasswordRequired` | Password env var missing and not optional |\n| `ErrSessionExists` | SetNX returned false (key already exists) |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Coverage Requirements\n\n| Module | Target Coverage | Priority |\n|--------|-----------------|----------|\n| pkg/router | 90% | High |\n| pkg/store | 95% | High |\n| pkg/picod | 90% | High |\n| pkg/common/types | 100% | Medium |\n\n### Test Categories\n\n#### Unit Tests (Pure Logic)\n\n**router:**\n- JWT token generation/validation with various claims\n- Error type methods (Status, Code, Message, Error, Unwrap)\n- Config defaults and validation\n- Reverse proxy URL building logic\n- Entry point selection algorithm\n- Key generation (sessionKey)\n\n**store:**\n- Store interface implementation correctness\n- Error type equality checking\n- Key prefix constants\n- Singleton pattern (Storage/ResetStorage)\n- Environment variable parsing (makeRedisOptions, newValkeyStoreFromEnv)\n\n**picod:**\n- Path sanitization (valid paths, traversal attacks, symlinks)\n- File mode parsing (valid octal, invalid, too high)\n- JWT public key loading (PEM decode, PKIX parse)\n\n#### Integration Tests (HTTP Handlers)\n\n**router:**\n- Server initialization with various configs\n- Route registration verification\n- Health endpoints (live/ready with various states)\n- TLS configuration (missing cert/key)\n- Graceful shutdown behavior\n- Concurrency limit enforcement\n- Proxy request handling with mock backends\n\n**picod:**\n- Execute handler (success, timeout, exit codes, working dir, env)\n- File operations (upload, list, download)\n- Authentication flow (valid/expired/invalid tokens)\n- Health check endpoint\n- Concurrent operations safety\n\n#### Mock-Based Tests\n\n**Required Mock Types:**\n\n```go\n// pkg/router mocks\ntype MockStore struct {\n    GetSandboxBySessionIDFunc     func(ctx, sessionID) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandboxFunc              func(ctx, *SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandboxFunc             func(ctx, *SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionIDFunc  func(ctx, sessionID) error\n    UpdateSessionLastActivityFunc func(ctx, sessionID, time) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxesFunc      func(ctx, time, int64) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxesFunc     func(ctx, time, int64) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)\n    PingFunc                     func(ctx) error\n    CloseFunc                    func() error\n}\n\ntype MockSessionManager struct {\n    GetSandboxBySessionFunc func(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n\ntype MockLogger struct {\n    InfoCalls, ErrorCalls, WarningCalls []string\n}\n\ntype MockHTTPClient struct {\n    DoFunc func(*http.Request) (*http.Response, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Test Helper Functions\n\n```go\n// pkg/router helpers\nfunc setupTestRouter(t *testing.T, opts ...Option) *Server\nfunc makeTestRequest(method, path, body) *http.Request\nfunc makeTestSandbox(sessionID string) *types.SandboxInfo\n\n// pkg/store helpers (existing)\nfunc setupTestRedisStore(t *testing.T) *redisStore\nfunc setupTestValkeyStore(t *testing.T) *valkeyStore\n\n// pkg/picod helpers (existing)\nfunc setupTestServer(t *testing.T) *Server\nfunc generateTestRSAKey(t *testing.T) (*rsa.PrivateKey, string)\nfunc generateTestJWT(privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey, expired bool) string\nfunc makeAuthenticatedRequest(t, server, method, path, body, contentType, jwtToken)\n```\n\n### Table-Driven Test Patterns\n\n```go\n// Example: StoreSandbox table-driven test\nfunc TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name    string\n        sandbox *types.SandboxInfo\n        wantErr error\n        setup   func(*redisStore)\n    }{\n        {\"nil sandbox\", nil, ErrNilSandbox, nil},\n        {\"empty sessionID\", &SandboxInfo{SessionID:\"\", ExpiresAt:time.Now()}, ErrEmptySessionID, nil},\n        {\"zero expiresAt\", &SandboxInfo{SessionID:\"test\", ExpiresAt:time.Time{}}, ErrZeroExpiresAt, nil},\n        {\"duplicate\", makeTestSandbox(\"dup\"), ErrSessionExists, func(s){s.StoreSandbox(ctx, makeTestSandbox(\"dup\"))}},\n        {\"valid\", makeTestSandbox(\"valid\"), nil, nil},\n    }\n    \n    store := setupTestRedisStore(t)\n    ctx := context.Background()\n    \n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            if tt.setup != nil { tt.setup(store) }\n            err := store.StoreSandbox(ctx, tt.sandbox)\n            if tt.wantErr != nil {\n                assert.ErrorIs(t, err, tt.wantErr)\n            } else {\n                assert.NoError(t, err)\n            }\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n### Test File Organization\n\n```\npkg/\n├── router/\n│   ├── server.go              └── server_test.go          # 380 lines, 15+ tests\n│   ├── config.go              └── config_test.go          # Need to add\n│   ├── jwt.go                 └── jwt_test.go             # Need comprehensive tests\n│   ├── errors.go              └── errors_test.go          # 189 lines, 14 tests (100%)\n│   ├── middleware.go          └── middleware_test.go      # 305 lines, 13 tests\n│   ├── session_manager.go     └── session_manager_test.go # 366 lines, 12 tests\n│   ├── reverse_proxy.go       └── reverse_proxy_test.go   # Need to add\n│   ├── doc.go\n│\n├── store/\n│   ├── store.go               └── store_test.go           # 759 lines, 45+ tests\n│   ├── store_redis.go         │\n│   ├── store_valkey.go        └── valkey_test.go          # Need comprehensive tests\n│   ├── doc.go\n│\n├── picod/\n│   ├── server.go              │\n│   ├── config.go              │\n│   ├── auth.go                └── auth_test.go            # Need edge cases\n│   ├── execute.go             └── execute_test.go         # Need edge cases\n│   ├── files.go               └── files_test.go           # Need edge cases\n│   ├── sanitize.go            └── sanitize_test.go        # Covered in picod_test.go\n│   ├── health.go              │\n│   ├── picod_test.go          # 1109 lines, 50+ tests (comprehensive)\n│   ├── doc.go\n│\n└── common/\n│   └── types/\n│       ├── sandbox.go         └── sandbox_test.go         # Need validation tests\n│       └── doc.go\n```\n\n### Current vs Required Tests\n\n| Module | File | Current Lines | Current Tests | Required Tests |\n|--------|------|---------------|---------------|----------------|\n| router | server_test.go | 380 | 15+ | ✓ Adequate |\n| router | config_test.go | - | 0 | Add: DefaultConfig, validation |\n| router | jwt_test.go | - | 0 | Add: GenerateToken, ValidateToken, Refresh, Key loading |\n| router | errors_test.go | 189 | 14 | ✓ Complete |\n| router | middleware_test.go | 305 | 13 | ✓ Adequate |\n| router | session_manager_test.go | 366 | 12 | ✓ Adequate |\n| router | reverse_proxy_test.go | - | 0 | Add: Director, ErrorHandler, URL building |\n| store | store_test.go | 759 | 45+ | ✓ Comprehensive |\n| store | valkey_test.go | - | 0 | Add: Match Redis coverage |\n| picod | picod_test.go | 1109 | 50+ | ✓ Comprehensive |\n| picod | auth_test.go | - | 0 | Add: Concurrent key update |\n| picod | execute_test.go | - | 0 | Add: Command not found, large output |\n| picod | files_test.go | - | 0 | Add: Overwrite, special chars |\n| types | sandbox_test.go | - | 0 | Add: Validate() tests |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Test Dependencies\n\n```go\n// go.mod test dependencies\nrequire (\n    github.com/stretchr/testify v1.9.0      // assert, require\n    github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2 v2.33.0 // Redis mock\n    github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0        // HTTP framework (test mode)\n    github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.7.0     // Redis client\n    github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go v1.0.0   // Valkey client\n    github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.0     // JWT handling\n)\n```\n\n### Import Patterns\n\n```go\n// Standard test imports\nimport (\n    \"testing\"\n    \"context\"\n    \"time\"\n    \"net/http/httptest\"\n    \"encoding/json\"\n    \n    \"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n    \"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n    \"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n    \"github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Running Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all pkg tests\ngo test ./pkg/... -v\n\n# Module-specific tests\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v\ngo test ./pkg/store/... -v\ngo test ./pkg/picod/... -v\n\n# With coverage\ngo test ./pkg/... -cover -coverprofile=coverage.out\ngo tool cover -func=coverage.out\ngo tool cover -html=coverage.out\n\n# Race detection\ngo test ./pkg/... -race\n\n# Specific test\ngo test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManager -v\n```\n\n### miniredis Usage\n\n```go\nfunc setupTestRedisStore(t *testing.T) *redisStore {\n    mr := miniredis.RunT(t)  // Auto-cleanup with t.Cleanup\n    cli := redisv9.NewClient(&redisv9.Options{Addr: mr.Addr()})\n    return &redisStore{\n        cli: cli,\n        sessionPrefix: \"session:\",\n        expiryIndexKey: \"session:expiry\",\n        lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Gin Test Mode\n\n```go\nfunc TestExample(t *testing.T) {\n    gin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)  // Required for consistent behavior\n    \n    router := gin.New()\n    router.GET(\"/test\", handler)\n    \n    w := httptest.NewRecorder()\n    req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/test\", nil)\n    router.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n    \n    assert.Equal(t, 200, w.Code)\n}\n```\n\n### Environment Variable Cleanup\n\n```go\nfunc setupWithEnv(t *testing.T, key, value string) {\n    old := os.Getenv(key)\n    os.Setenv(key, value)\n    t.Cleanup(func() {\n        if old != \"\" {\n            os.Setenv(key, old)\n        } else {\n            os.Unsetenv(key)\n        }\n    })\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Spec: `changes/AR-039/spec.md`\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-039/delta-spec.md`\n- Proposal: `changes/AR-039/proposal.md`\n- Tasks: `changes/AR-039/tasks.md`\n- client-go Spec: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n- Test Files:\n  - `pkg/router/server_test.go` (380 lines)\n  - `pkg/router/errors_test.go` (189 lines)\n  - `pkg/router/middleware_test.go` (305 lines)\n  - `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` (366 lines)\n  - `pkg/store/store_test.go` (759 lines)\n  - `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` (1109 lines)"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/agentd/main.go\">\nERROR [8:2] \"time\" imported and not used\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/server.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":156,"character":52},"end":{"line":156,"character":63}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/server_test.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/auth_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":246,"character":3},"end":{"line":246,"character":16}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://staticcheck.dev/docs/checks/#QF1003"},"source":"QF1003","message":"could use tagged switch on idx % 3"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/agentd/main.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":7,"character":1},"end":{"line":7,"character":7}},"severity":1,"code":"UnusedImport","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#UnusedImport"},"source":"compiler","message":"\"time\" im